Former Gauteng Health MEC Bandile Masuku. JOHANNESBURG - Nurses organisation, Denosa says the work of former Gauteng Health MEC, Bandile Masuku has been overshadowed by the PPE scandal. Denosa says the reputation of the Health department had improved under Masuku’s leadership. Gauteng Premier David Makhura fired Masuku on Friday. This followed a report finding by the Special Investigating Unit on PPE irregularities that Masuku had failed to execute his duties in compliance with the Constitution and the Public Finance Management Act. READ: Masuku plans to challenge SIU report Makhura's says he'll reinstate Masuku if the final SIU investigation clears him but Denosa says Makhura must be more decisive and stop tiptoeing around issues. The organisation says it's in the interest of stability for the Gauteng health department. Denosa's special Provincial Executive Committee concluded on Saturday.